The Port Elizabeth Magistrate s Court will this morning hear the bail application of controversial Nigerian pastor Tim Omotoso.Omotoso has been in custody at St Albans Prison since April. His new attorney, James Riley, is expected to present fresh facts that will show why he qualifies to be released on bail.The court denied Omotoso bail last month, agreeing with the state that he was a flight risk and could interfere with the ongoing investigation.Omotoso was arrested by the Hawks in dramatic fashion in April at the Port Elizabeth International Airport on allegations of sexual exploitation and human trafficking.He faces 22 charges relating to sexual exploitation and human trafficking after 18 more charges were added to the original four.He is alleged to have sexually abused several young women at his church in Durban.-NONDUMISO ZWANE